com.mousebird.maply

Class VectorStyleProcessor

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.mousebird.maply.VectorStyleProcessor

  • public class VectorStyleProcessor
extends java.lang.Object
    Provides a static method to run vectors through a vector style. This can be used as a standalone to visualize vectors from any source that's converted to a list of VectorObjects.

      • UseStyle

        public static ComponentObject[] UseStyle(VectorObject[] vecObjs,
                                         VectorStyleInterface styleGen,
                                         RenderControllerInterface vc)
        Use the given style to turn the vector objects into visual components. Looking for at least a "layer" or "layer_name" for each object. Can work anyway.
        Parameters:
        vecObjs - Vector objects to process.
        styleGen - Style to use in processing them
        vc - Controller to build the features against.
        Returns:
        ComponentObjects created for the visuals.
